        "summary": "Security review",
        "excerpt": "# Security Review\n\nThis review focuses on the active deception runtime, local file boundaries, and LLM-assisted planning/generation paths.\n\n## Executive Summary\n\n- The strongest existing controls are scoped real-read roots in `InterceptionLayer`, fallback-safe strategy generation, and now canonical decoy path validation. Sources: [core/interception_layer.py#L14](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/core/interception_layer.py#L14), [core/path_resolver.py#L46](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/core/path_resolver.py#L46), [agents/strategy/strategy_agent.py#L62](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/agents/strategy/strategy_agent.py#L62).\n- The largest remaining security risks are incomplete decoy coverage that falls back to real reads, console logging of sensitive operational context, and limited auditability around generated deception content. Sources: [core/interception_layer.py#L103](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/core/interception_layer.py#L103), [core/decision_engine.py#L21](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/core/decision_engine.py#L21), [logs/logger.py#L32](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/logs/logger.py#L32).\n\n## File Access and Path Traversal\n\n- Finding: decoy writes needed canonical boundary validation. This is now fixed with `abspath` and `commonpath` checks. Sources: [core/path_resolver.py#L34](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/core/path_resolver.py#L34), [core/path_resolver.py#L50](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/core/path_resolver.py#L50).\n- Finding: real reads are already limited to `shared`, `demo_shared`, and optional `REAL_READ_ROOTS`. Sources: [core/interception_layer.py#L17](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/core/interception_layer.py#L17), [core/interception_layer.py#L24](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/core/interception_layer.py#L24), [core/interception_layer.py#L46](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/core/interception_layer.py#L46).\n- Remaining risk: if the operator adds a broad `REAL_READ_ROOTS`, the deception layer can legitimately serve real content from that scope when confidence is low or no decoy exists. Sources: [core/interception_layer.py#L25](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/core/interception_layer.py#L25), [core/decision_engine.py#L21](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/core/decision_engine.py#L21).\n- Minimal recommendation: warn at startup when `REAL_READ_ROOTS` points to very broad locations such as a user profile root or repository root.\n\n## Prompt Injection and Unsafe LLM Output\n"
      },
      {
        "path": "PRODUCTION_READINESS_REPORT.md",
        "exists": true,
        "size": 4367,
        "modified": "2026-06-09T05:46:28.291Z",
        "summary": "Production readiness",
        "excerpt": "# Production Readiness Report\n\n## Summary\n\nThe repository has a coherent end-to-end architecture and a working local runtime, but it was closer to a strong research prototype than a production-ready service. This pass improved startup validation, decoy path safety, cache correctness, generated-content correctness, and regression coverage without changing the architecture. Sources: [README.md#L19](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/README.md#L19), [main.py#L33](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/main.py#L33), [core/path_resolver.py#L46](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/core/path_resolver.py#L46), [tests/test_production_hardening.py#L1](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/tests/test_production_hardening.py#L1).\n\n## Improvements Applied\n\n- Startup now validates config shape and required model artifacts before the infinite loop begins. Sources: [main.py#L33](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/main.py#L33), [main.py#L55](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/main.py#L55).\n- Decoy filesystem resolution now rejects traversal outside `decoy_env`. Source: [core/path_resolver.py#L46](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/core/path_resolver.py#L46).\n- Generation fallback behavior now keeps disk, cache, and returned content aligned. Sources: [agents/generation/generation_agent.py#L142](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/agents/generation/generation_agent.py#L142), [agents/generation/generation_agent.py#L163](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/agents/generation/generation_agent.py#L163).\n- Live process events now expose `cmd_entropy` end to end for model scoring parity. Sources: [agents/event_enrichment.py#L252](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/agents/event_enrichment.py#L252), [logs/logger.py#L196](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/logs/logger.py#L196).\n- Added focused regression tests around the above changes. Source: [tests/test_production_hardening.py#L1](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/tests/test_production_hardening.py#L1).\n\n## Ready Areas\n\n- Core orchestration is explicit and easy to follow through the LangGraph node graph. Sources: [langgraph_pipeline.py#L58](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/langgraph_pipeline.py#L58), [langgraph_pipeline.py#L72](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/langgraph_pipeline.py#L72).\n- The system already has a useful validation harness in `run_all_checks.ps1`. Sources: [run_all_checks.ps1#L139](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/run_all_checks.ps1#L139), [run_all_checks.ps1#L315](/E:/agentic_ai/defense system/run_all_checks.ps1#L315)."
      },
